## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 6 |
| **High** | 1 |
| **Medium** | 1 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called, giving 95%+ line coverage, but **most tests verify nothing**. Bugs in `UpdatePrice`, `RemoveProduct`, `ApplyBulkDiscount`, and `ImportFromCsv` would never be caught.

---

### 🔴 Critical — Tests giving false confidence

#### 1. No Assertions (systematic coverage touching)

**6 out of 10** tests have zero meaningful assertions. They execute code purely to hit coverage counters:

| Test Method | Lines | Problem |
|---|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` | 19–21 | No assertion that the product was actually stored |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | 33–36 | Never checks the price changed |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | 39–43 | Never checks the product was removed |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | 64–66 | Never asserts the count value |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | 69–74 | Never verifies discounted prices |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | 85–88 | Never checks the product was imported |

**Fix — example for each:**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_StoresProductRetrievableBySku()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var retrieved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(product, retrieved);
}

[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ChangesStoredPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
}

[TestMethod]
public void RemoveProduct_MakesProductUnretrievable()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

    Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
}

[TestMethod]
public void GetProductCount_ReturnsNumberOfStoredProducts()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));

    Assert.AreEqual(1, _catalog.GetProductCount());
}

[TestMethod]
public void ApplyBulkDiscount_ReducesPricesByFraction()
{
